{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Break"], "type": "title", "extent": [31, 41], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [41, 110], "text": ["Breaks the input geometry using the specified cutting shape."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [110, 467], "text": ["This tool cuts a model along a jagged cutting plane. The cutting plane can also be switched to a box, sphere, or custom object. You can then use the pieces with the ", {"text": ["RBD Fractured Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject"}, " or ", {"text": ["RBD Glue Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject"}, ". This will automatically clean up the faces, and unique the points so you don\u2019t see the cracks."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [467, 693], "text": [{"text": ["RBD Fractured Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject"}, " and ", {"text": ["RBD Glue Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject"}, " automatically add an ", {"text": ["Assemble"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/assemble", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/assemble"}, " node after any breaks, which creates groups for each piece of broken geometry."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [693, 835], "text": ["The Break tool creates a single jagged cut with manual control, whereas ", {"text": ["Shatter"], "fullpath": "/shelf/shatter", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/shatter"}, " creates multiple random cuts automatically."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [841, 880], "text": ["This tool only works on polygons."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [835, 841], "container": true, "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "extent": [910, 951], "text": ["Select the object you want to break."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1030, 1125], "text": ["You can do this multiple times to create multiple breaks in a single geometry object."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1125, 1162], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/break.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/break.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/break", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/break"}, {"text": ["Break"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/break", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/break"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Model"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."], "extent": [951, 1030], "container": true, "blevel": 2, "type": "ord"}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1168, 1402], "text": ["By default, the Break tool will select connected primitives. If you want to select individual faces, right-click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/TOOLS/select_faces", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "TOOLS/select_faces"}, " component mode button on the left toolbar and turn off ", {"text": ["Select Connected Geometry"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1162, 1168], "container": true, "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1402, 1543], "text": ["You can then turn your object into an ", {"text": ["RBD Fracture Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdfracturedobject"}, " or an ", {"text": ["RBD Glue Object"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject"}, ".    "]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1548, 1755], "text": ["If you want to simulate pieces breaking off of something else, for example rocks breaking off a cliff, you can use the ", {"text": ["extract"], "fullpath": "/shelf/extract", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/extract"}, " tool to separate the static objects from dynamic objects."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1543, 1548], "container": true, "type": "tip"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1755, 1975], "text": ["If you do not want to use this tool with dynamics, you will need to append an ", {"text": ["Assemble SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/assemble", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/assemble"}, ". Turning the object into an RBD Fracture Object or an RBD Glue Object will create the Assemble node for you."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using Break"], "extent": [880, 910], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "includeme"}], "summary": ["Breaks the input geometry using the specified cutting shape."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"tags": "model", "icon": "SOP/break"}, "title": ["Break"]}